                            <comment id="233949" author="adilger" created="Tue, 25 Sep 2018 08:20:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In fact, &lt;tt&gt;llapi_layout_from_lum()&lt;/tt&gt; already exists, but it is currently a static internal interface that is passed a &quot;&lt;tt&gt;struct lov_user_md&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; but that often isn&apos;t even the real structure type. It would be more useful to have the proposed &lt;tt&gt;llapi_layout_get_by_xattr(char *lov_user_md, size_t lum_size)&lt;/tt&gt; interface as a thin wrapper for the internal interface.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
